180
00:35:18,758 --> 00:35:26,500
[SPEAKER_00]: This program brought presenters into the schools with over $100,000 worth of original 18th century artifacts and reenactments

181
00:35:27,067 --> 00:35:32,549
[SPEAKER_00]: of the soldiers during the Revolutionary War to help bring what the students are learning in the classroom to real life.

182
00:35:33,769 --> 00:35:41,571
[SPEAKER_00]: The MEF was also able to fund in part a grant to spearhead an innovation to bring hydroponics to the elementary school level.

183
00:35:42,151 --> 00:35:49,333
[SPEAKER_00]: Started by McGlynn principal Diane Guarino and fourth grade teacher Donna Lasky, fourth grade students are learning about hydroponics.

184
00:35:49,754 --> 00:35:54,795
[SPEAKER_00]: And while the students are having fun, they are also realizing how what they learn in science, math, and social studies

185
00:35:55,214 --> 00:35:56,795
[SPEAKER_00]: applies to real-world problems.

186
00:35:57,536 --> 00:36:14,648
[SPEAKER_00]: At the middle school level, we were happy to fund a garden project by social studies teacher Kathleen O'Donoghue, who is teaching her 6th, 7th, and 8th grade students about how to build a sustainable food source in an urban setting and also learn about providing healthy food for themselves and their families.

187
00:36:15,528 --> 00:36:22,333
[SPEAKER_00]: At the high school level, we are helping to expand the existing successful aquaponics fish tank to include a hydroponics system.

188
00:36:22,717 --> 00:36:25,758
[SPEAKER_00]: so that the plants will clean the water and the fish will fertilize the plants.

189
00:36:26,398 --> 00:36:44,065
[SPEAKER_00]: In addition, we are funding programs that target at-risk students through the Empower Student Club at the high school and teach real-world skills through Nicholas Kane's excellent docent teaching training program and teaching publishing skills through turning the online student mantra magazine into a print version.

190
00:36:44,786 --> 00:36:48,207
[SPEAKER_00]: In total, we were able to fund three grants at the elementary school level,

191
00:36:48,708 --> 00:36:52,031
[SPEAKER_00]: one at the middle school level, and seven at the high school and vocational school.

192
